Here is a TekAutomate Steps UI flow that connects to your MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, recalls (saves) the setup to C:/setups/test.set, takes a screenshot, and then disconnects.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "label": "Connect to Scope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": [],
        "printIdn": true
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "recall",
      "label": "Save Setup to C:/setups/test.set",
      "params": {
        "filename": "C:/setups/test.set",
        "operation": "save"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "save_screenshot",
      "label": "Save Screenshot",
      "params": {
        "filename": "capture.png",
        "scopeType": "modern",
        "method": "pc_transfer"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "label": "Disconnect from Scope",
      "params": {
        "instrumentIds": []
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow will:
1. Connect to the oscilloscope.
2. Save the current setup to the specified path.
3. Capture a screenshot and save it as capture.png.
4. Disconnect from the oscilloscope.

Let me know if you want to change the screenshot filename or add more steps!

